node.text:
Tetris gone Metal by Doctor P. 🎸🤘🏼 with @positivegrid Spark

Trying to switch things up with my tone. It’s been awesome playing with sounds with my Spark amp. Still have lots to learn, but I’m able to experiment with tones I would have never thought of on my own. It’s been a great learning experience.

Click the link in my bio to get $40 off your Spark now!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KIKI WONG in Los Angeles, California with @officialjacksonguitars, and @akanet91. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
There are two things that will truly define you:
1) Patience when you have nothing 
2) Your attitude when you have everything

No matter how crazy life gets or how amazing things become, how much you win, how much you lose, don’t lose yourself in the process. 

Hang in there. Stay amazing. ❤️

node.text:
No bad vibes, only bad girl vibes. 😈 New Hair by @akanet91 

But how do you go about living your live bad vibe free?

The thing is as much as we’d like to feel we are in control of the things that make us fulfilled or happy, we aren’t. Life throws way too many curveballs and obstacles while some of us are still learning to use the tee. 

Don’t rely on others to give you the vibes you want. The only way you can live life with less bad vibes is:

1. Choose to the best of your ability an environment with the least amount of negativity. 

2. Make your own vibes so damn good there isn’t room for bad ones. 

Not everybody has the ability or choice to pick their environment. However, you always have control over how you react to a situation. Are you going to look at those bad vibes as an attack, weakness, and something that brings you down? Or are you going to make it your strength, your superpower, your determination to be a better version of yourself?

The choice is yours. You got this. ❤️💪
